# Boardroom MCP — local environment. NEVER commit real values.
#
# Phase-1 auth pivot: the production Supabase instance is Lovable-owned
# (ref loiavmastgeieqyiwyyr) and does NOT expose a service-role key to us.
# So the server logs in as the advisor via signInWithPassword using the
# publishable key. Consequences — both improvements:
#   * RLS is the real enforcement from day one (advisor policies gate access).
#   * No god-key (service-role) ever sits on the laptop.
#
# The publishable key is RLS-safe (no privileges of its own). The advisor
# credentials are secrets — keep them only in your local, untracked mcp/.env.
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
MCP_ADVISOR_EMAIL=
MCP_ADVISOR_PASSWORD=

# OPTIONAL — leave empty. The service-role key does not exist for the
# Lovable-owned prod instance, so createServiceRoleContext is unusable here.
# Only set this if the instance is ever migrated to our own Supabase.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
